ies to collapse and form a neutron star. Calculations such as\nthese are an important step in producing more realistic progenitor models for\nstudies of the signature of accretion-induced collapse.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2015 20:01:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 7 Aug 2015 14:25:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 10 Aug 2016 22:18:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-12"}
