pendent on BH and torus masses and the exact\ntreatment of shear viscosity. The combined ejecta of CBM and BH-torus phases\ncan reproduce the solar abundances amazingly well for A>90. Varying\ncontributions of the torus ejecta might account for observed variations of\nlighter elements with 40<Z<56 relative to heavier ones, and a considerable\nreduction of the prompt ejecta compared to the torus ejecta, e.g. in highly\nasymmetric NS-BH mergers, might explain the composition of heavy-element\ndeficient stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2015 14:35:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Oct 2015 10:01:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-13"}
{"id":"1504.05449","submitter":"Michael I. Weinstein","authors":"Michael I. Weinstein","title":"Localized States and Dynamics in the Nonlinear Schroedinger /\n  Gross-Pitaevskii Equation","comments":"To appear in Frontiers in Applied Dynamics: Reviews and Tutorials,\n  Volume 3 (Springer, 2015) 40 pages, 9 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.PS cond-mat.mes-hall math-ph math.AP math.MP quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This article is a review of results on the nonlinear Schroedinger /\nGross-Pitaevskii equation (NLS / GP). Nonlinear bound states and aspects of\ntheir stability theory are discussed from variational and bifurcation\nperspectives. Nonlinear bound states, in the particular cases where the\npotential is a single-well, double-well potential and periodic potential, are\ndiscussed in detail. We then discuss particle-like dynamics of solitary wave\nsolutions interacting with a potential over a large, but finite, time interval.\nFinally we turn to the very long time behavior of solutions. We focus on the\nimportant resonant radiation damping mechanism that drives the relaxation of\nthe system to a nonlinear ground state and underlies the phenomena of {\\it\nGround State Selection} and {\\it Energy Equipartition}. We also analyze linear\nand nonlinear \"toy minimal models\", which illustrate these mechanisms.\nRegarding the overall style of this article, we seek to emphasize the key ideas\nand therefore do not present all technical details, leaving that to the\nreferences.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2015 14:48:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-04-22"}
